    • NO_PERMISSION

      public final String NO_PERMISSION
      No-Permission message. Appears when the player tried to execute a BaseCommand or a SubCommand, but he doesn't have the permission for it.

    • USAGE

      public final String USAGE
      Usage message. Appears when the player used a command wrong according to its Syntax.

    • ONLY_PLAYER

      public final String ONLY_PLAYER
      Only-Player message. Appears when the console tried to use a command that is player-only.

    • USAGE_REASON_REQUIRED

      public final String USAGE_REASON_REQUIRED
      A reason text that is provided by Simpler. Appears when the player didn't provide a ArgumentPriority.REQUIRED argument.
